The following rules apply only to React and Next.js projects.

Naming Conventions:
• Use PascalCase for React components. Example: ChatBot
• Use camelCase for utility functions and variables. Examples: sendEmail, agentName
• Use kebab-case for page file names and routing folders inside the app/ directory. Example: agent-configuration
• Use UPPER_CASE for environment variables. Example: API_KEY
• Use camelCase for root-level folder names. Example: globalComponents
• Use PascalCase for database table names. Example: AgentConfigurations
• Use PascalCase for database field names. Example: AgentId
• Use camelCase for function names. Example: getAgent()

Technologies to Use (React/Next.js projects only):
Typescript
React.js
MUI
Zustand
Axios
Prettier

Code Editor Formatting Rules:
• All functions should use arrow function syntax
• Use tabs for indentation
• Tab width should be 4 spaces
• Use single quotes for all strings
• Do not use trailing commas
• Always use semicolons
